  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If you have a function that returns a struct, you cannot do this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexpect (await contract.getPoint(0)).to.deep.equal({x: 1, y: 2})\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe reason is that the object returned by ethers is something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  0: 1,\r\n  1: 2,\r\n  length: 2,\r\n  x: 1,\r\n  y: 2\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis means users have to either compare the result field by field, or convert the ethers value to something that can actually be compared.\r\n\r\nTwo ideas:\r\n- Detect that an object like this is being compared, and ignore the properties that are \"array-like\". We can't distinguish this in the general case (maybe some user just happens to have an object like this), but I think we can have an heuristic that is right 99.9999% of the time.\r\n- If we can't do that for any reason, we could have a new matcher. Something like `.equalStruct` maybe.",
